    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Grid Independence Study for CFD Hemolysis Model",
    "description": "A systematic grid independence study was conducted using three mesh refinement levels (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 5.8M cells, fine: 14.3M cells) to demonstrate that discretization error in the hemolysis index prediction falls below the 2% threshold required at MRL 2. Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the grid convergence index (GCI) for wall shear stress and velocity magnitude at critical impeller locations. The study confirmed that the medium mesh achieves GCI < 1.8% for all quantities of interest, satisfying the discretization error factor requirement.",
    "activityType": "GridConvergenceStudy",
